\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy establishes mandatory standards for internal and external communications conducted by the Elko County Information Operations Department.
 It defines formal versus informal communication boundaries,
 promotes transparency and accountability,
 and ensures consistent stakeholder engagement across governance,
 operational,
 and service contexts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Information Operations personnel,
 including full-time employees,
 part-time staff,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 and volunteers.
 It governs communications with:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Board of County Commissioners,
 County Manager,
 and Administrative leadership.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Elected Officials,
 Department Heads,
 and department leadership staff.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Third-party vendors,
 service providers,
 and contractors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Regulatory,
 compliance,
 and auditing bodies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The public and media (only where explicitly authorized).
\end_layout

